<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-05-12T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-05-12T10:00:00-05:00" n="220" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d220">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/806: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-05-12T23:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">May 12,
                                        1928—11 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received May 12—9:25
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>343. Your 146, May 4, 10 [<hi rend="italic">5</hi>] p.m. Consul at Chefoo
                            reports Dr. Gaston categorically refuses to comply with instructions of
                            mission board. Webber suggests that board be requested to cable Gaston
                            direct ordering withdrawal.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>